Installation:
1) Place contents of this directory in your moodle/filter directory.
2) Download ChemAxons "Marvin for Web Developers" and install in directory called marvin at your web root.
If you don't want to install there make change to filter.php.
3) Visit your sites Notification to update database and install filter.
4) If you haven't done so already download and install tinymce plugin moodle-tinymce_eomarvin2d.

Use:  This filter opens all ChemAxons Marvin .mrv data between <mar></mar> tags with 2D MarvinView applet. 
